(## Module 5: Study Plan & Practice Exercises) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### 1\) Ordered study plan for a new learner) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(1. Read `README.md` for goals, stage order, and expected artifacts.) Tj
T*
(2. Read `pyproject.toml` for dependencies and Python/tooling constraints.) Tj
T*
(3. Read `settings.py` and both YAML files to understand config contract and defaults.) Tj
T*
(4. Read `schemas.py` and `data.py` to learn target schema and how datasets are built.) Tj
T*
(5. Read `datasets.py` to understand tokenization, truncation, masking, and padding.) Tj
T*
(6. Read `models.py` and `train.py` to understand LoRA/QLoRA and DPO loops.) Tj
T*
(7. Read `evaluate.py` to learn parsing and metric calculations.) Tj
T*
(8. Read `run_pipeline.py` last to connect all pieces end-to-end.) Tj
T*
(9. Read `tests/` to confirm intended behavior for split generation and JSON extraction utility.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
